'''customs'''
# ({{plural}}) The plural of "[[custom]]"
#: ''The [[w:Ancient Egypt|Ancient Egyptian]] culture had many [[queer]] and [[interesting]] beliefs and '''customs'''.''
# ({{plural}}) The [[duty|duties]] or [[tax]]es [[impose]]d on [[import]]ed [[goods]].
#: ''We had to pay '''customs''' of £200 on all the [[wine]] we took back from France.''
# ({{singular}}) The [[government]] [[department]] or [[agency]] that is [[authorise]]d to [[collect]] the [[tax]]es [[impose]]d on [[import]]ed [[goods]].
#: ''We got pulled over by '''customs''' on our way back from France - we only had 200 bottles of [[wine]] - it was so unfair.''

